      <Desc>AFTER SECURING APPROVAL FOR PITTSBURGH'S FIRST CITY-WIDE AFFORDABLE HOUSING TRUST FUND, THE HOUSING OPPORTUNITY FUND (HOF), IN DECEMBER OF 2016, OUR HOUSING JUSTICE CAMPAIGN WILL BE WORKING CLOSELY WITH POLICY MAKERS TO DETERMINE THE BEST WAY TO FUND THE HOF AND ENSURE COMMUNITY INPUT.</Desc>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
        <Desc>IN LIGHT OF SEVERAL EXPENSIVE AND DANGEROUS MISSTEPS BY THE LOCAL WATER AUTHORITY, THE OUR WATER CAMPAIGN AND CLEAN RIVERS CAMPAIGN, FOCUSED ON ENVIRONMENTAL JUSTICE, WILL CONTINUE TO FIGHT FOR SAFE, AFFORDABLE, PUBLICLY CONTROLLED WATER IN PITTSBURGH AND INVESTMENT IN GREEN INFRASTRUCTURE IN OUR NEIGHBORHOODS.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp>
        <Desc>WE'VE VERY RECENTLY EXPANDED INTO SEVERAL LOCAL COUNTIES, OUR SHORT TERM AIM IS TO BUILD RELATIONSHIPS IN THOSE AREAS AND TAKE ON THE CAMPAIGNS THAT THE LOCAL COMMUNITY DICTATES IS MOST IMPORTANT TO ITS EQUITABLE SURVIVAL. OUR LONG TERM AIM IS TO BUILD REGIONAL POWER AND CLAIM A LARGER STAKE IN THE WRITING AND IMPLEMENTATION OF STATEWIDE POLICY.</Desc>
